<br>
I think we've got the feel of the hidden side of floor 3 well enough to do a hot drop now.  Or maybe I just like the term &quot;hot drop&quot;?  Hmmmm.....  Really, with a full party, buffed to the gills, we can drop the well and quickly establish a beachhead.  Maybe we could throw Kizor in first, with an invisibility on, to scout it out.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Then we can just beat the troll down and take his keys and his lunch money.<br>
<br>
We also need to camp the troll SK for a bit to get a BBC (bone-bladed claymore, 2HS) for anybody that wants one.  This thing has a tremendous damage rate for a 20th level drop.  Plus it's really big, and the ladies dig it.  Or so I keep telling myself.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Friday, Saturday, and Sunday are all open for me.  Time of day isn't really an issue in Befallen.  I don't know if people are scared of it, or what, but I haven't seen more than a dozen people in there at any time of day.  My preference would be to start in the late evening, say 6 or 7 EDT, (as these things always seem to run late) on Friday or Saturday.  I'll do the coordination to let Gwion's brain cool off after the scavenger hunt.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Post your time preferences/availibilities here, or mail to me at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: FinraelOfFelwithe@hotmail.com"> FinraelOfFelwithe@hotmail.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END-->.  <br>
<br>
